description:
Current quota implementation relies on volume node to commit reservation, which would break when scheduling fails.   And there's no way a following 'delete' API can rollback that quota reservation.  Cinder doesn't do a minus reservation when deleting volume that failed to schedule neither.  Therefore, quota reservation is leaking when scheduling fails.

To reproduce this issue:

1. stop and disable all volume nodes;
2. create a volume A;
3. delete volume A;
4. check quotas table in DB.

